main_definition: Alternative spelling of staunch ( “ that which stanches; act of stanching ” ) .

definitions.definition: A floodgate by which water is accumulated , for floating a boat over a shallow part of a stream by its release ; also, a dam or lock in a river .

main_definition: A floodgate by which water is accumulated , for floating a boat over a shallow part of a stream by its release ; also, a dam or lock in a river .
